  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Genjutsu (Doujutsu)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 6 (Spell Level 3)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 4</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 20 | <b>Successes:</b> 4</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 8 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 21</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> C, Mas</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>This technique can only be used while your Sharingan ability is active. The subject becomes fascinated (p13) by your eyes, staring into your sharingan and dropping anything it is holding. You can concentrate on this technique no more than 3 rounds after your Sharingan is disabled, even if the duration would allow for it.<br><br>While fascinated, the subject has a 5% chance of having any rage or frenzy effect on them ended each round, and you gain a +2 bonus to Charisma-based checks made against them. Each round, the subject can make an additional save to end the technique.<br><br>This technique can be used once per day.</p>\n\n\n<p><b>Mastery:</b> The second and fourth steps increases the number of uses per day by one each.</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
